# Example CLAUDE.md — Full HESOYAM Stack

> This is a complete, real-world CLAUDE.md showing all five pillars working together.
> Copy this into your project root and customize.

---

# Project: Meridian — Team Collaboration Platform

## Stack
- Next.js 15 (App Router) + TypeScript (strict)
- Tailwind CSS v4 + Radix UI primitives
- tRPC for type-safe API layer
- PostgreSQL via Prisma ORM
- Redis for caching + Pub/Sub
- Resend for transactional email
- Stripe for billing
- Vercel for deployment

## Architecture Rules
- Server Components by default. Client Components only for interactivity (`'use client'`).
- Server Actions for mutations. No API routes for internal CRUD.
- tRPC for complex queries that need caching or pagination.
- Zod schemas shared between client and server — single source of truth.
- All money amounts as integers (cents). Display with `Intl.NumberFormat`.

## Code Conventions
- Named exports only (except pages/layouts)
- Path aliases: `@/` maps to `src/`
- Feature-based folder structure under `src/features/`
- Barrel exports via `index.ts` per feature
- No `any` type. No `as` type assertions (use type guards instead).
- Error boundaries at feature boundaries, not every component.

## File Structure
```
src/
├── app/                    # Next.js App Router (pages, layouts)
├── features/
│   ├── auth/               # Authentication
│   ├── workspaces/         # Multi-tenant workspaces
│   ├── channels/           # Real-time messaging
│   ├── billing/            # Stripe integration
│   └── notifications/      # In-app + email notifications
├── components/
│   ├── ui/                 # Radix UI wrapper components
│   └── shared/             # Cross-feature components
├── lib/                    # Utilities, clients, configs
├── server/                 # tRPC routers, server-only logic
└── styles/                 # Global Tailwind config
```

## Testing
- Vitest for unit tests (co-located: `*.test.ts`)
- Playwright for E2E (in `e2e/`)
- MSW for API mocking
- Coverage target: 80% on business logic, skip UI snapshot tests

## Commands
```
pnpm dev              # Start dev server
pnpm build            # Production build
pnpm test             # Run Vitest
pnpm test:e2e         # Run Playwright
pnpm db:migrate       # Prisma migrate dev
pnpm db:studio        # Prisma Studio
pnpm lint             # ESLint + TypeScript check
pnpm stripe:listen    # Forward Stripe webhooks locally
```

## Security
- All Stripe webhooks verified via signature. Idempotency keys on all mutations.
- Row-Level Security mindset: every DB query scoped to workspace. No global queries.
- CSRF protection via SameSite cookies + Origin header validation.
- Rate limiting on auth endpoints (5 attempts / 15 min).
- Secrets in environment variables only. Never in code, never in CLAUDE.md.

---

# HESOYAM Configuration

## Pillar I: Orchestration (oh-my-claudecode)

### Default Mode
Ralph Mode for most work. Deep Interview before any feature touching billing or auth.

### Execution Preferences
```
- Autopilot: Bug fixes, simple CRUD features
- Deep Interview: Auth flows, billing, data migrations
- Team Mode: Cross-cutting refactors (e.g., changing the auth model)
- Ecomode: Long research sessions, documentation updates
```

### Stop Callbacks
Notify on Slack (#eng-claude-notifications) when any session exceeds 30 minutes.

## Pillar II: Configuration (everything-claude-code)

### Installed Agents
```
agents/
├── code-reviewer.md         # TypeScript + React patterns
├── security-reviewer.md     # OWASP + Stripe-specific checks
├── architect.md             # App Router architecture decisions
├── tdd-guide.md             # Vitest-first workflow
└── e2e-runner.md            # Playwright execution
```

### Hooks
```json
{
  "PreToolUse": [
    {
      "matcher": "Bash",
      "hook": "block-no-verify"
    },
    {
      "matcher": "Bash",
      "hooks": [{ "type": "command", "command": "detect-secrets" }]
    },
    {
      "matcher": "Write|Edit",
      "hooks": [{ "type": "command", "command": "check-no-any-type" }]
    }
  ],
  "PostToolUse": [
    {
      "matcher": "Write|Edit",
      "hooks": [{ "type": "command", "command": "auto-lint" }]
    }
  ]
}
```

### Token Budget
- Max MCPs active: 6 (GitHub, Prisma, Stripe, Resend, Slack, Vercel)
- Max agents loaded: 5
- Manual compact at ~120K tokens used
- Subagents for any exploration task > 3 queries

## Pillar III: Memory (claude-mem)

### Signal Keywords
```json
["decided", "architecture", "auth", "billing", "migration",
 "security", "performance", "stripe", "bug", "tradeoff"]
```

### Weekly Promotion
Every Friday: `/promote-to-vault` — extract decisions and debug journals to Obsidian.

## Pillar IV: Knowledge (Obsidian)

### Vault Location
`~/vaults/meridian/`

### Key Vault Sections
```
01_Projects/meridian/        # Active sprint notes
02_Areas/
├── architecture/            # ADRs (ADR-001 through ADR-012)
├── billing/                 # Stripe integration decisions
└── security/                # Auth model, threat model
03_Resources/
├── debugging-journal/       # Past bugs and their root causes
├── patterns/                # Reusable code patterns
└── tech-decisions/          # Technology evaluations
```

### Obsidian Skills Enabled
- Note search and creation
- Daily note management
- Decision record creation from session context

## Pillar V: Discovery

### Monthly Review
First Monday of each month: scan awesome-claude-code for new skills relevant to our stack.

### Tracked Catalogs
- awesome-claude-code (main)
- awesome-claude-code-subagents (for new agent patterns)
- awesome-claude-skills (for Composio integrations)
